{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d190a2c1-6575-459d-bdef-3adc7a3f53ac","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed *above* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01W3r7eEt5gEkLmEXG1cTvWK","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-6e1ff0e7270140759f7a4c1a75150834/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-6e1ff0e7270140759f7a4c1a75150834/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"5c089343-b3a8-41d0-8731-eddef9f63687","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\nThe fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":369,"requestId":"782B:3738F9:F9E27:135C6F:69F549F4"},"id":"8933e18d-ef99-46c1-9156-172c8c6c7c3d","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:49:00.930Z","parentId":"6ff55b00-fb3b-4891-b819-7d6820a11c72"}
